<p>optking was aborting prematurely.  I just pushed the fix to the problem.  For this case I found consecutive_backsteps = 2 [or more], as well as dynamic_level = 1 to now be helpful.  (Don't use both at once as that is somewhat redundant.)  Sometime I will type up some tips on problematic optimizations.  But now optking will at least move you substantially closer to the minimum.  Though one may always have to restart an optimization, these options will minimize the manual effort necessary.</p>

